The paper deals with graph drawing and graph classes, which are topics typically studied in computational geometry (cs.CG) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also establishes relationships between SC and SOC graphs and other graph classes, such as string graphs and unit-interval graphs, which are topics studied in graph theory (cs.DS) and graph algorithms (cs.GT). Additionally, the paper discusses cop number and cliquewidth, which are topics studied in computational complexity (cs.SI).
